Reporter:<i> Intensive care units</i>
<i> across the country</i>

00:32.909 --> 00:34.800
<i> are reaching capacity,</i>

00:34.802 --> 00:37.928
<i> and hospital morgues are</i>
<i> filling at an alarming rate.</i>

00:37.930 --> 00:40.581
<i> Medical and government</i>
<i> officials are joining forces</i>

00:40.583 --> 00:44.401
<i> to try to quell what is</i>
<i> quickly becoming an epidemic.</i>

00:44.403 --> 00:46.996
<i> We are hearing report</i>
<i> after report</i>

00:46.998 --> 00:48.998
<i> of grisly attacks in hospitals</i>

00:49.000 --> 00:52.835
<i> by patients who are no longer</i>
<i> in control of their faculties.</i>

00:52.837 --> 00:56.580
<i> We are seeing sick people</i>
<i> no longer seeking medical care</i>

00:56.582 --> 00:58.933
<i> because of violence</i>
<i> erupting from patients</i>

00:58.935 --> 01:01.343
<i> no longer in their right minds.</i>

01:01.345 --> 01:11.353
♪♪

01:11.355 --> 01:21.363
♪♪

01:21.365 --> 01:30.873
♪♪

01:30.875 --> 01:32.191
♪♪

01:32.193 --> 01:34.193
Man: No!

01:34.195 --> 01:35.636
No!

01:35.638 --> 01:37.863
No! Oh, God!

01:37.865 --> 01:40.215
[Chuckles]

01:40.217 --> 01:43.627
No! No!

01:43.629 --> 01:48.390
[Whimpering]

01:48.392 --> 01:51.043
Come on!
Let's go!

01:51.045 --> 01:53.637
[Grunts]

01:53.639 --> 01:55.047
Don't be afraid,
George.

01:55.049 --> 01:56.882
Don't be afraid.

01:56.884 --> 01:59.885
Remember, the end
is the beginning.

01:59.887 --> 02:02.629
You're about to be given
a new life.

02:02.631 --> 02:06.341
You actually believe all
the bullshit you spew, Maddox?

02:06.343 --> 02:07.668
Get it all out.

02:07.670 --> 02:10.880
You'll be walking this walk
soon enough.

02:10.882 --> 02:12.731
[Door opens]

02:12.733 --> 02:14.508
[Door closes]

02:14.510 --> 02:16.510
♪♪

02:16.512 --> 02:19.847
[Chuckles]

02:19.849 --> 02:24.668
♪♪

02:24.670 --> 02:26.187
Oh.

02:26.189 --> 02:28.672
[Spoon clatters]

02:28.674 --> 02:30.399
Ah.

02:31.527 --> 02:34.862
[Alarm blaring, doors clanging]

02:34.864 --> 02:40.183
[Indistinct shouting]

02:40.185 --> 02:44.538
[Growling]

02:44.540 --> 02:47.099
[Shouting continues]

02:47.101 --> 02:49.451
[Screaming in distance]

02:49.453 --> 02:52.605
Man: Guards! Guards!
Open the door!

02:52.607 --> 02:54.456
Man #2:
Hey! Stop!

02:54.458 --> 02:57.385
[Alarm continues]

02:57.387 --> 03:01.389
[Walkers growling]

03:01.391 --> 03:03.799
[Man groans in distance]

03:03.801 --> 03:06.118
Aah!

03:06.120 --> 03:08.470
Aah! Aah!

03:08.472 --> 03:14.476
[Screaming,
shouting in distance]

03:14.478 --> 03:20.182
♪♪

03:20.184 --> 03:24.094
[Growling]

03:24.096 --> 03:26.972
[Whimpers]

03:26.974 --> 03:32.569
♪♪

03:32.571 --> 03:33.954
[Grunts]

03:33.956 --> 03:36.123
[Grunts]

03:36.125 --> 03:37.425
[Growling stops]

03:37.427 --> 03:39.001
[Alarm continues]

03:39.003 --> 03:44.098
♪♪

03:44.100 --> 03:46.267
I was right. I was right.

03:46.269 --> 03:48.436
I just needed to be patient.

03:48.438 --> 03:53.165
[Man groaning]

03:53.167 --> 03:56.301
It's not bullshit, Hayes.

03:56.303 --> 03:59.188
It's revelation.

03:59.190 --> 04:02.341
[Groans]
Oh, God.

04:02.343 --> 04:05.861
[Screaming]

04:05.863 --> 04:15.871
♪♪

04:15.873 --> 04:20.468
♪♪

04:23.472 --> 04:25.714
Teddy:
<i> You have been here before.</i>

04:25.716 --> 04:30.369
<i> You have lived this moment</i>
<i> before.</i>

04:30.371 --> 04:33.055
<i> We don't want to believe that,</i>
<i> do we?</i>

04:33.057 --> 04:36.650
<i> We don't want to accept</i>
<i> the circularity.</i>

04:36.652 --> 04:41.805
<i> But believe me when I tell you,</i>
<i> my friends, we are in a loop.</i>

04:41.807 --> 04:43.732
<i> You have been here before.</i>

04:43.734 --> 04:48.721
<i> You have lived this moment</i>
<i> before.</i>

04:48.723 --> 04:51.481
<i> We don't want to believe that,</i>
<i> do we?</i>

04:51.483 --> 04:53.408
<i> You have been here before.</i>

04:53.410 --> 04:56.411
<i> You have lived this moment</i>
<i> before.</i>

04:56.413 --> 04:57.654
<i> [Echoing] ...before.</i>

04:57.656 --> 04:59.489
<i> We are in a loop.</i>

04:59.491 --> 05:01.491
<i> We are in a loop.</i>

05:01.493 --> 05:02.401
<i> ...in a loop.</i>

05:02.403 --> 05:03.177
<i> ...in a loop.</i>

05:03.179 --> 05:04.678
<i> ...in a loop.</i>

05:04.680 --> 05:07.923
[Door opens]

05:07.925 --> 05:11.685
<i> This world wears its ugliness</i>
<i> on its sleeve.</i>

05:11.687 --> 05:13.503
<i> It has told us who it is.</i>

05:13.505 --> 05:16.431
Are you ready
to accept his word?

05:16.433 --> 05:18.584
<i> Accept the pattern.</i>

05:18.586 --> 05:20.343
<i> Or break it.</i>

05:20.345 --> 05:23.179
<i> We</i> can<i> break it.</i>

05:23.181 --> 05:25.699
[Scoffs]
<i> We must break it,</i>

05:25.701 --> 05:28.327
<i> or we're doomed to repeat it.</i>

05:29.947 --> 05:32.540
<i> You have been here before.</i>

05:32.542 --> 05:35.934
<i> You have lived this moment</i>
<i> before.</i>

05:35.936 --> 05:37.436
[Door opens]

05:37.438 --> 05:39.621
<i> We don't want to believe that,</i>
<i> do we?</i>

05:39.623 --> 05:43.425
<i> This world wears its ugliness</i>
<i> on its sleeve.</i>

05:43.427 --> 05:45.201
<i> It has told us who it is.</i>

05:45.203 --> 05:47.780
<i> And it leaves us with a choice.</i>
[Sighs]

05:47.782 --> 05:49.798
<i> Accept the pattern.</i>

05:49.800 --> 05:51.784
<i> Or break it.</i>
Or break it.

05:51.786 --> 05:54.544
<i> We</i> can<i> break it.</i>

05:54.546 --> 05:58.974
<i> We must break it,</i>
<i> or we're doomed to repeat it.</i>

05:58.976 --> 06:02.577
[Birds chirping]

06:02.579 --> 06:04.054
[Door opens]

06:04.056 --> 06:07.032
[Door creaks]

06:13.324 --> 06:15.231
You stopped sending
your errand boy.

06:15.233 --> 06:17.084
You stopped
eating your beans.

06:17.086 --> 06:18.586
[Door creaks]

06:18.588 --> 06:19.978
[Chuckles]

06:19.980 --> 06:22.089
This wasn't my preferred

06:22.091 --> 06:24.908
method of induction for you,
you know.

06:24.910 --> 06:26.718
Locking me up
like a prisoner?

06:26.720 --> 06:28.578
I was locked up
myself once.

06:28.580 --> 06:32.825
Oh, I thought it was
the end of the road for me.

06:32.827 --> 06:35.177
[Chuckles] Turns out,
it was just the opposite.

06:35.179 --> 06:37.420
I'd hoped that, uh,

06:37.422 --> 06:39.773
it would yield
the same revelation for you.

06:41.669 --> 06:42.943
Sorry to disappoint.

06:42.945 --> 06:45.613
Oh, but I-I do bring
good news.

06:45.615 --> 06:47.114
We've found our new home.

06:47.116 --> 06:50.676
The others are packing up
to head there as we speak.

06:50.678 --> 06:53.195
Oh, this place
has served its purpose,

06:53.197 --> 06:58.208
but we needed, eh,
something safer, sturdier,

06:58.210 --> 07:02.278
somewhere we could, uh,
truly begin again.

07:02.280 --> 07:03.964
You know?

07:03.966 --> 07:07.635
Now, before we take our first
steps together, Alicia,

07:07.637 --> 07:11.805
I need some assurances
from you

07:11.807 --> 07:14.383
that you are, um...
[Chuckles]

07:14.385 --> 07:17.311
I don't know,
dedicated,

07:17.313 --> 07:20.205
committed to
what we're doing here.

07:20.207 --> 07:22.298
Well, you're not
gonna get them.

07:22.300 --> 07:25.711
What am I gonna get
from you?

07:25.713 --> 07:27.154
I don't know.

07:27.156 --> 07:29.381
Something you
probably won't like.

07:29.383 --> 07:30.732
[Chuckles]
[Gun cocks]

07:30.734 --> 07:32.818
Riley: We're wasting our time
with her.

07:32.820 --> 07:34.569
Riley.
She's never gonna
see the truth.

07:34.571 --> 07:36.813
Riley.
Let's end this
right here.

07:36.815 --> 07:38.282
Let's leave her behind.

07:38.284 --> 07:40.158
No. No.

07:40.160 --> 07:42.068
She's coming with me.

07:42.070 --> 07:45.230
Surprising what you pick up
on death row, huh?

07:45.232 --> 07:47.157
[Groans]

07:47.159 --> 07:50.844
♪♪

08:03.693 --> 08:05.192
Where are you taking her?

08:07.029 --> 08:10.439
[Gas can clatters]

08:10.441 --> 08:12.758
I have a personal matter
to attend to.

08:12.760 --> 08:15.310
I want her
to accompany me.

08:15.312 --> 08:18.764
Why her?

08:18.766 --> 08:22.101
I would like to get to know her
a bit better, Riley.

08:22.103 --> 08:25.771
I have a feeling
she is going to be critical

08:25.773 --> 08:28.698
for our new beginning.

08:28.700 --> 08:31.510
Don't question me
about her again.

08:34.615 --> 08:37.266
[Vehicle approaches]

08:38.953 --> 08:40.227
[Brakes squeal]

08:40.229 --> 08:43.705
[Chuckles]

08:43.707 --> 08:44.957
Who are they?

08:44.959 --> 08:47.100
New recruits
we picked up on our scouts.

08:47.102 --> 08:48.568
Welcome, welcome.

08:48.570 --> 08:51.113
You all are gonna see
our new home, huh?

08:52.491 --> 08:54.833
Dakota?

08:54.835 --> 08:56.318
Alicia?

08:56.320 --> 08:57.911
Teddy:
She a friend of yours?

08:57.913 --> 08:59.413
It's not the word
I'd use.

08:59.415 --> 09:02.324
She killed
someone I knew.

09:02.326 --> 09:04.601
Why?

09:04.603 --> 09:07.570
Something that
had to be done.

09:07.572 --> 09:10.274
Have you
come to us alone?

09:10.276 --> 09:11.817
No family?

09:11.819 --> 09:13.719
She actually
tried to kill her mother.

09:15.556 --> 09:17.931
Did you succeed?

09:17.933 --> 09:19.266
I didn't.

09:19.268 --> 09:20.826
Someone else did.

09:20.828 --> 09:22.936
[Chuckles]
A woman after my own heart.

09:22.938 --> 09:24.480
You hop in.
You're coming with us.

09:24.482 --> 09:26.089
I'm not going anywhere
with her.

09:26.091 --> 09:28.442
I'm afraid you're not at liberty
to make that call.

09:28.444 --> 09:31.403
If you're smart,
you wouldn't bring her.

09:31.405 --> 09:33.447
You shouldn't go
with either of them.

09:33.449 --> 09:34.740
Yeah, I'll be fine.

09:36.118 --> 09:38.243
Alright,
alright, alright.

09:47.371 --> 09:51.023
Now, if I don't show up
by tomorrow,

09:51.025 --> 09:53.025
you know what to do.

09:53.027 --> 09:55.093
Now, come on.
Let's go see what we got, huh?

09:58.290 --> 10:00.549
Listen, Alicia, this isn't
what it looks like.

10:00.551 --> 10:03.626
It wasn't the last time,
either.

10:03.628 --> 10:06.814
This is different.

10:06.816 --> 10:08.982
I went looking for you
in the city.

10:08.984 --> 10:10.651
I followed them
on all their scouting missions

10:10.653 --> 10:12.227
as best as I could,

10:12.229 --> 10:14.379
hoping that you'd be
on one of them, but you weren't,

10:14.381 --> 10:16.882
so I got in with them,
told them I wanted to join.

10:16.884 --> 10:18.383
I came here
to help you.

10:18.385 --> 10:20.886
I don't want
your help.

10:20.888 --> 10:23.889
I don't need
your help.

10:23.891 --> 10:27.409
I left after I heard
what happened underground.

10:27.411 --> 10:29.628
Alicia,
it's getting really bad.

10:29.630 --> 10:31.413
Morgan tried to bring
everyone together

10:31.415 --> 10:32.822
to try and figure out
how to beat these people,

10:32.824 --> 10:34.007
but I think
it's getting worse.

10:34.009 --> 10:36.659
I'm not listening
to you.

10:36.661 --> 10:38.178
I want to make up
for what I did.

10:38.180 --> 10:40.830
I need to, Alicia.

10:40.832 --> 10:43.333
Whether you believe me
or not.

10:43.335 --> 10:46.094
I heard them talking about
the place they're going,

10:46.096 --> 10:47.913
that it's stocked with
so many supplies

10:47.915 --> 10:50.399
that they wouldn't even have to
step outside for years.

10:53.087 --> 10:54.686
We can kill him.

10:54.688 --> 10:56.938
He is scary as hell,
but he's old.

10:56.940 --> 10:58.607
We could do it.

10:58.609 --> 11:00.826
You know, he's stupid
for not believing who we are.

11:03.931 --> 11:07.766
There is no we here.

11:07.768 --> 11:09.418
There never will be.

11:13.774 --> 11:15.365
Just stay
out of my way.

11:15.367 --> 11:16.775
You want to know
what he's up to,

11:16.777 --> 11:18.126
where it is
that he's going,

11:18.128 --> 11:20.262
why he's got those keys
on his necklace.

11:21.557 --> 11:23.131
So,
what are you gonna do?

11:23.133 --> 11:24.391
[Keys jingling]

11:24.393 --> 11:26.226
Teddy:
Shall we?

11:27.229 --> 11:29.304
[Chuckles]

11:29.306 --> 11:30.838
Alright.

11:30.840 --> 11:34.026
[Truck door squeaks]

11:46.140 --> 11:49.458
[Scoffs]

11:51.253 --> 11:52.753
This isn't gonna work.

11:52.755 --> 11:54.146
What isn't?

11:54.148 --> 11:56.665
Bringing me out here
is not gonna break me.

11:56.667 --> 11:59.334
I don't understand.
Oh, cut the shit.

11:59.336 --> 12:01.503
I know you listened to
all the recordings Riley made.

12:01.505 --> 12:03.096
Somebody told you
about the stadium?

12:03.098 --> 12:04.580
Who was it?
Luciana?

12:04.582 --> 12:06.350
What, the stadium?
The place I used to live.

12:06.352 --> 12:08.101
Oh,
with your mother.

12:08.103 --> 12:10.845
The place where you told me
she -- she grew the crops?

12:10.847 --> 12:13.832
Oh, you expect me to believe
this is just all a coincidence?

12:13.834 --> 12:15.517
There are no coincidences.

12:15.519 --> 12:17.352
The universe
sends us signs,

12:17.354 --> 12:19.296
and it's up to us
to interpret them.

12:19.298 --> 12:21.039
Dakota: Like what?

12:21.041 --> 12:24.284
Well, I don't think it's
an accident you're here, Sioux.

12:24.286 --> 12:26.361
Sioux?
Sioux Falls.

12:26.363 --> 12:28.956
It's my favorite city
in the Dakotas.

12:28.958 --> 12:32.942
But your arrival,
or the timing of it, I--

12:32.944 --> 12:34.703
it's for a reason.

12:34.705 --> 12:36.296
And what's that?

12:36.298 --> 12:39.758
Well, these things tend
to reveal themselves.

12:49.703 --> 12:52.938
[Scraping]

12:59.405 --> 13:01.396
Yeah.

13:01.398 --> 13:03.282
Can you
give me a hand?

13:06.161 --> 13:07.828
Yeah. Oh.

13:10.482 --> 13:14.376
Oh. Oh.

13:15.912 --> 13:18.029
[Lid creaks]

13:18.031 --> 13:21.383
Oh. Oh.

13:29.834 --> 13:31.810
Hello, Mother.

13:34.248 --> 13:37.415
Mother?

13:37.417 --> 13:40.009
How did she die?

13:40.011 --> 13:44.089
She was taken
way before her time.

13:44.091 --> 13:46.274
No, but that doesn't mean
that she can't be

13:46.276 --> 13:47.926
part of
our new beginnings.

13:47.928 --> 13:56.618
♪♪

13:56.620 --> 14:00.863
When we're finished,
all this...

14:00.865 --> 14:02.865
will be gone.

14:02.867 --> 14:09.681
♪♪

14:15.639 --> 14:17.230
This is why you brought us
out here?

14:17.232 --> 14:20.125
To dig up
your mother's corpse?

14:20.127 --> 14:23.236
Look, all three of us
have lost mothers,

14:23.238 --> 14:27.407
and I wanted both of you
to help me accompany mine

14:27.409 --> 14:29.083
back to our new home.

14:29.085 --> 14:30.726
Dakota: Why?

14:30.728 --> 14:34.081
God, I wanted to break these
patterns for such a long time.

14:34.083 --> 14:35.898
I told my mother
I was gonna do it

14:35.900 --> 14:39.068
and wound up in a prison cell
condemned to death.

14:39.070 --> 14:41.146
I thought I'd just...

14:41.148 --> 14:42.481
failed.

14:42.483 --> 14:45.667
Every night, in my --
in my cell,

14:45.669 --> 14:48.786
I-I looked at this.

14:48.788 --> 14:51.747
Disgusted with myself
for what I'd done.

14:51.749 --> 14:53.325
I thought
I got it wrong.

14:53.327 --> 14:54.935
It was all
for nothing.

14:54.937 --> 14:57.920
But then I realized
I wasn't wrong.

14:57.922 --> 15:01.349
I just needed
to be patient.

15:01.351 --> 15:03.259
And then...

15:03.261 --> 15:05.261
it happened.

15:05.263 --> 15:06.521
What happened?

15:06.523 --> 15:08.865
The world changed,
and with it...

15:08.867 --> 15:11.009
[Chuckles]
my freedom,

15:11.011 --> 15:13.695
and a chance
to reshape the world

15:13.697 --> 15:16.289
into everything
I believed it could be,

15:16.291 --> 15:21.294
where I could preserve
everything I...loved

15:21.296 --> 15:24.506
and destroy
everything I didn't.

15:28.637 --> 15:30.862
You think you can do all that
with a pair of keys?

15:30.864 --> 15:33.473
[Chuckles]

15:34.560 --> 15:36.709
What do they unlock?

15:36.711 --> 15:38.386
Oh.

15:38.388 --> 15:41.222
Our future.

15:41.224 --> 15:43.541
You're really starting
to sound like my mom.

15:43.543 --> 15:45.944
[Tires screech]

15:49.733 --> 15:52.033
W-- Mother!

15:52.035 --> 15:53.735
Oh!
Oh, God!

15:53.737 --> 15:55.328
Oh, my God!

15:58.141 --> 16:01.393
Mother.

16:01.395 --> 16:03.395
Oh.

16:03.397 --> 16:05.338
Mother.

16:07.342 --> 16:08.733
It'll be alright.

16:08.735 --> 16:10.402
Would you please come here

16:10.404 --> 16:12.670
and help me get her
back onto the truck?

16:12.672 --> 16:16.183
Please.

16:17.761 --> 16:20.169
Right. Okay. Alright.

16:20.171 --> 16:22.171
There we go.
[Smooches]

16:22.173 --> 16:24.024
Teddy.
It's okay. What?

16:24.026 --> 16:26.860
[Walkers growling]

16:26.862 --> 16:28.253
Oh.
Don't.

16:28.255 --> 16:29.529
You'll draw more.

16:31.024 --> 16:33.258
♪♪

16:33.260 --> 16:35.293
Take that.

16:35.295 --> 16:44.544
♪♪

16:44.546 --> 16:46.521
A-ha.

16:46.523 --> 16:51.885
♪♪

16:51.887 --> 16:53.386
[Gunshot]

16:53.388 --> 16:54.787
[Gunshot]

16:54.789 --> 16:56.130
[Gunshot]

16:56.132 --> 16:58.466
[Body thuds, gun cocks]

16:58.468 --> 17:03.396
♪♪

17:03.398 --> 17:06.458
Cole?

17:06.460 --> 17:08.843
Alicia?

17:08.845 --> 17:11.137
Is that you?

17:11.139 --> 17:13.798
I was gonna ask you
the same question.

17:13.800 --> 17:18.511
♪♪

17:18.513 --> 17:21.264
Who the hell is that?

17:21.266 --> 17:23.250
An old friend.

17:23.252 --> 17:24.918
What kind of old friend?

17:24.920 --> 17:26.461
Her mom...

17:26.463 --> 17:29.314
is the only reason
I ain't one of these skinbags.

17:29.316 --> 17:31.925
Your mother,
huh?

17:31.927 --> 17:33.668
How's that for a sign?

17:33.670 --> 17:37.389
♪♪

17:42.511 --> 17:45.563
[Birds chirping]

17:50.003 --> 17:52.595
Riley, are you there?

17:52.597 --> 17:55.740
We are in need of some
roadside assistance.

17:59.121 --> 18:02.438
Riley, do you copy?

18:02.440 --> 18:03.773
Uh...

18:03.775 --> 18:07.018
I'm gonna see if
I fare any better...

18:07.020 --> 18:09.020
up the road a bit.

18:09.022 --> 18:10.922
Come on.

18:13.376 --> 18:15.710
I can't believe
it's you.

18:15.712 --> 18:17.011
[Chuckles]

18:17.013 --> 18:20.031
You been on the --
the road?

18:20.033 --> 18:21.975
Yeah.

18:21.977 --> 18:25.312
Long time,
Alicia.

18:25.314 --> 18:27.205
We spent weeks
looking for you all.

18:27.207 --> 18:28.798
When we didn't find you,
well, we just thought

18:28.800 --> 18:32.468
you must've died
in the fire, too.

18:32.470 --> 18:34.045
Wait, "we"?

18:34.047 --> 18:35.822
Doug. Viv.

18:35.824 --> 18:38.641
Bunch of us from the stadium are
still around thanks to your mom,

18:38.643 --> 18:40.051
what she did.

18:40.053 --> 18:42.329
[Chuckles]

18:42.331 --> 18:43.955
How's your brother?

18:48.895 --> 18:50.462
I'm sorry.

18:53.991 --> 18:58.828
Luciana,
she's still alive.

18:58.830 --> 19:01.348
Victor, too.

19:01.350 --> 19:04.351
Where are they?

19:04.353 --> 19:06.870
Luci lives at
the same place I do.

19:06.872 --> 19:09.022
Victor...

19:09.024 --> 19:11.674
went his own way.

19:11.676 --> 19:13.768
He always does.

19:13.770 --> 19:16.512
What you doing out this way,
Alicia?

19:16.514 --> 19:17.772
You must've come
from far.

19:17.774 --> 19:20.683
All this gas
you're carrying.

19:20.685 --> 19:22.827
You don't see
much of that these days.

19:27.100 --> 19:29.450
Teddy's been stocking up
on some supplies for a while.

19:29.452 --> 19:31.936
Who is he?
What's his deal?

19:31.938 --> 19:34.105
I'm still trying to
figure it out.

19:34.107 --> 19:36.007
Teddy:
No signal.

19:38.053 --> 19:40.703
I don't suppose you know
where we could, uh,

19:40.705 --> 19:42.681
find a new car,
do you?

19:47.287 --> 19:49.378
There's an old
auto parts shop nearby.

19:49.380 --> 19:51.055
But I wouldn't go there
on your own.

19:51.057 --> 19:52.607
It's not safe
around here.

19:52.609 --> 19:54.200
Seen these before.

19:54.202 --> 19:56.861
How they set them
for people passing through.

19:58.381 --> 20:00.240
"They"?

20:00.242 --> 20:02.967
Unsavory types.

20:02.969 --> 20:04.469
Take whatever they want.

20:04.471 --> 20:06.705
I was out on a food run,
I ran into a bunch of them.

20:06.707 --> 20:08.990
Been trying to get back
to my people ever since.

20:08.992 --> 20:12.310
A lot of the dead you see
around here, they killed them,

20:12.312 --> 20:14.312
left them
looking like Swiss cheese.

20:14.314 --> 20:15.905
After they took
what they wanted.

20:15.907 --> 20:17.457
I'll get you
where you need to go.

20:17.459 --> 20:18.925
I know
which roads to take.

20:18.927 --> 20:21.761
You don't need
to do that.
I believe he does.

20:24.891 --> 20:28.268
Lead the way.

20:28.270 --> 20:31.521
I am gonna need, uh,
your gun, though.

20:34.517 --> 20:36.517
I'm not handing anything
to you.

20:36.519 --> 20:37.835
Alright.

20:37.837 --> 20:40.721
Hand it to her,
then.

20:40.723 --> 20:43.098
[Chuckles]
I'm beginning to trust you.

20:43.100 --> 20:45.952
I just want to make sure
we can trust<i> him.</i>

20:45.954 --> 20:55.520
♪♪

20:55.522 --> 20:56.704
♪♪

20:56.706 --> 20:58.606
It's alright.

20:58.608 --> 21:08.549
♪♪

21:08.551 --> 21:14.055
♪♪

21:14.057 --> 21:17.400
[Growling]

21:19.337 --> 21:20.945
[Grunts]

21:24.684 --> 21:26.567
How long
were you locked up?

21:26.569 --> 21:28.978
Mm,
almost 30 years.

21:28.980 --> 21:30.813
What did you do
to get in there?

21:30.815 --> 21:33.574
Mm, I killed some people
who got in my way,

21:33.576 --> 21:36.986
people who didn't see the world
the way I did.

21:36.988 --> 21:38.654
My mom locked me up.

21:38.656 --> 21:40.915
Did everything she could
to get me away from people.

21:40.917 --> 21:42.233
[Chuckles]

21:42.235 --> 21:43.510
Did you know
any of them?

21:43.512 --> 21:45.345
A few.

21:45.347 --> 21:47.180
Did you feel bad
killing them?

21:47.182 --> 21:49.565
Do I detect some guilt

21:49.567 --> 21:53.186
over your own
acts of malice, Sioux?

21:53.188 --> 21:55.246
I only
killed people I had to.

21:55.248 --> 21:57.840
So, you knew them,
then?

21:57.842 --> 22:01.528
One of them
more than the others.

22:01.530 --> 22:03.271
You know, for a bit,
he was kinda

22:03.273 --> 22:04.697
starting to become
like family.

22:04.699 --> 22:08.442
Did you feel bad
about what you did to him?

22:08.444 --> 22:10.261
No.

22:10.263 --> 22:13.022
Didn't really give me
much of a choice.

22:13.024 --> 22:14.949
But when
I tell people that,

22:14.951 --> 22:16.676
they look at me
like they're scared.

22:16.678 --> 22:18.861
But from what I can tell,
that's just how things are now.

22:18.863 --> 22:21.272
Oh, but people --
yeah, you don't frighten people.

22:21.274 --> 22:24.033
I mean, they're frightened
by what you're saying

22:24.035 --> 22:25.777
'cause they know
it's the truth.

22:25.779 --> 22:27.036
And you're right.

22:27.038 --> 22:29.280
It is the way of things now.
[Chuckles]

22:29.282 --> 22:31.182
Cole:
This is it.

22:34.637 --> 22:37.397
You got my gun.

22:37.399 --> 22:39.640
We could take him out.
No, I can't.

22:39.642 --> 22:41.125
Not until I know
what he's doing.

22:41.127 --> 22:43.052
But if he's gone,

22:43.054 --> 22:46.573
doesn't seem like
there'll be much to worry about.

22:46.575 --> 22:49.867
He's got a group.
If he doesn't do it, they will.

22:51.896 --> 22:54.414
Any idea what "it" is?

22:57.419 --> 22:59.902
No, I don't know,
but it's gotta be something big.

22:59.904 --> 23:03.572
He and his followers
have been setting up a place,

23:03.574 --> 23:06.384
a bunker, with enough food
to last for years.

23:09.155 --> 23:12.748
You know,
you could join us.

23:12.750 --> 23:14.951
After you find out
whatever you need to.

23:14.953 --> 23:16.494
Me, Doug, Viv,
and the others,

23:16.496 --> 23:18.087
we got it pretty good
where we're at.

23:18.089 --> 23:19.513
Cole, I can't.

23:19.515 --> 23:22.683
I've been looking for a way
to pay back the favor

23:22.685 --> 23:24.961
for what Madison did
for me.

23:24.963 --> 23:28.263
Maybe running into you --
maybe this is it.

23:28.265 --> 23:30.700
Maybe I finally
found it.

23:40.870 --> 23:43.963
[Metal clinking]

23:50.847 --> 23:53.723
[Box rustles, thuds]

23:55.477 --> 23:58.719
Is there a problem?

23:58.721 --> 24:00.647
You remind of her.

24:02.484 --> 24:04.375
Who?

24:04.377 --> 24:06.486
[Inhales sharply]
Mother.

24:06.488 --> 24:08.488
My mother.

24:16.498 --> 24:18.906
Have you decided yet
what you're gonna do?

24:18.908 --> 24:21.976
You gonna
join us underground?

24:21.978 --> 24:24.504
No,
'cause you're wrong.

24:24.506 --> 24:26.530
[Clattering]

24:26.532 --> 24:28.490
Hands up.

24:28.492 --> 24:35.515
♪♪

24:35.517 --> 24:37.617
Cole?

24:37.619 --> 24:40.520
Those unsavory types?

24:40.522 --> 24:42.830
I'm one of 'em.

24:42.832 --> 24:45.766
♪♪

24:45.768 --> 24:47.710
You can
take them off now.

24:47.712 --> 24:52.014
♪♪

24:52.016 --> 24:54.183
Alicia: Viv?
Sorry, Alicia.

24:54.185 --> 24:56.185
Doug?

24:56.187 --> 24:57.611
Are you kidding me?
No.

24:57.613 --> 24:59.163
[Gun cocks]
We're not.

24:59.165 --> 25:01.766
♪♪

25:01.768 --> 25:05.186
Teddy: After her mother
saved your lives?

25:05.188 --> 25:07.438
Cole:
Yeah, well...

25:07.440 --> 25:09.531
maybe she should've
let us die.

25:09.533 --> 25:13.886
♪♪

25:25.958 --> 25:28.434
Cole: Wasn't lying when I said
I got attacked.

25:28.436 --> 25:30.403
We all did.

25:30.405 --> 25:34.240
We're the only ones who didn't
get shotgun shells to the gut.

25:34.242 --> 25:37.301
When?

25:37.303 --> 25:39.203
When?

25:42.617 --> 25:45.042
About a week after the fire
at the stadium.

25:51.317 --> 25:53.667
What happened?

25:53.669 --> 25:56.061
We were looking for a place
to hole up,

25:56.063 --> 25:58.322
to regroup so we could
come looking for you,

25:58.324 --> 26:04.086
and Nick,
and Victor and Luciana.

26:04.088 --> 26:06.998
Went into a motel
off 78,

26:07.000 --> 26:09.091
and there were some people
in there waiting for us.

26:09.093 --> 26:10.902
They killed most of us.

26:14.007 --> 26:16.616
Who's left?

26:16.618 --> 26:18.075
You're looking at us.

26:24.350 --> 26:26.700
So, you've decided to do
the same thing

26:26.702 --> 26:29.703
to whoever else
crosses your path?

26:29.705 --> 26:31.080
Teddy: This is
what I've been trying

26:31.082 --> 26:32.373
to get you to understand,
Alicia.

26:32.375 --> 26:35.359
The patterns
of the universe.

26:35.361 --> 26:37.536
It's because
of people like you, Cole,

26:37.538 --> 26:40.473
[Chuckles] that the world
needs to be destroyed.

26:40.475 --> 26:42.033
Hey.

26:42.035 --> 26:44.018
We ain't proud
of living like this,

26:44.020 --> 26:47.129
but it's all
we can do.

26:47.131 --> 26:48.630
We had another way.

26:48.632 --> 26:50.132
Cole: And you know
how that ended.

26:50.134 --> 26:53.677
We tried to find you,
to do something more

26:53.679 --> 26:56.564
than just look out
for ourselves.

26:56.566 --> 27:00.568
Then, well, most of us
were gone.

27:00.570 --> 27:04.122
So, we found this way,
and we're still standing.

27:05.908 --> 27:10.394
You became the people
we were always fighting off.

27:10.396 --> 27:12.396
There's always
bad people out there

27:12.398 --> 27:15.508
waiting to make things
go south.

27:15.510 --> 27:17.918
That is, south for you,
not for them.

27:17.920 --> 27:20.738
You know how we can fix it,
Alicia?

27:20.740 --> 27:22.664
Getting rid of them.
[Laughs]

27:22.666 --> 27:25.076
[Guns cock]
That seems
hard to do

27:25.078 --> 27:26.853
when you're on this end
of my shotgun.

27:26.855 --> 27:30.147
[Laughs]

27:31.584 --> 27:33.317
Keep walking,
Gramps.

27:49.785 --> 27:53.129
[Indistinct conversation]

27:55.550 --> 27:58.275
Hey, Alicia.

27:58.277 --> 28:02.037
I didn't come over here to rub
salt in your wounds, but, uh...

28:02.039 --> 28:04.448
I know what you're thinking
right now.

28:04.450 --> 28:07.284
Oh,
I highly doubt that.

28:07.286 --> 28:10.563
Eh, you're thinking your --
your mother died for something,

28:10.565 --> 28:12.565
and all the people
she saved

28:12.567 --> 28:16.460
are somewhere out there
living meaningful lives.

28:16.462 --> 28:18.738
But most of them
are dead,

28:18.740 --> 28:22.533
and the ones that aren't
are living like bottom feeders.

28:28.658 --> 28:30.199
This is what you want.

28:30.201 --> 28:32.585
Well, I don't want
to see you in pain.

28:32.587 --> 28:34.754
But you don't understand.

28:34.756 --> 28:36.589
We're both after
the same thing,

28:36.591 --> 28:39.074
for you to fulfill
your potential.

28:39.076 --> 28:41.594
The more I learn about you,
the more confident I am

28:41.596 --> 28:43.654
that you are the person
I've been looking for.

28:43.656 --> 28:46.248
You're delusional.
I...[Chuckles]

28:46.250 --> 28:48.083
But -- But you don't know
what it is

28:48.085 --> 28:49.343
I'm setting out
to do.

28:49.345 --> 28:50.844
No,
I have no idea.

28:50.846 --> 28:53.497
I've been trying to
figure that out for weeks...

28:53.499 --> 28:54.682
and I have no clue.

28:54.684 --> 28:57.501
No one does.
So, just tell me.

28:57.503 --> 28:58.961
When you're ready.

28:58.963 --> 29:00.337
Cole: Hey.

29:00.339 --> 29:02.097
Now, what is it about
guns pointed at you

29:02.099 --> 29:04.433
makes you think
you can take a break?

29:04.435 --> 29:06.010
We gotta move.

29:06.012 --> 29:08.353
Take the truck.
Take whatever you want in it.

29:08.355 --> 29:11.073
We'll walk out of here
and never both you again.

29:11.075 --> 29:12.441
Right?

29:12.443 --> 29:15.594
Mm, I don't make promises
I can't keep.

29:15.596 --> 29:17.279
Cole: No, we tried
playing nice once.

29:17.281 --> 29:19.281
And the assholes
we robbed,

29:19.283 --> 29:22.042
they came back
and nearly killed us.

29:22.044 --> 29:23.736
But this place
you're headed --

29:23.738 --> 29:25.620
man,
it sounds really nice.

29:25.622 --> 29:27.890
So, you won't mind telling us
exactly where it is.

29:30.436 --> 29:31.918
There's gotta be a map.

29:31.920 --> 29:35.206
Oh, no, you're not gonna
find anything in there.

29:35.208 --> 29:36.465
[Truck door opens]

29:36.467 --> 29:38.209
It's in there,
huh?

29:38.211 --> 29:40.544
'Cause I'd be more than happy
to open that up for you.

29:40.546 --> 29:42.905
Cole --
Why are you
protecting this asshole?

29:46.219 --> 29:48.068
Where is this place
you're going?

29:48.070 --> 29:49.519
Teddy.

29:49.521 --> 29:52.498
It's okay, Sioux.
It's okay.

29:52.500 --> 29:54.558
Doug: We've been here
way too long, Cole.

29:54.560 --> 29:56.502
All this noise --
it'll bring more dead.

29:56.504 --> 29:58.896
Forget him, Cole.
We've got a truck.

29:58.898 --> 30:00.673
We've got gas.
We've got food.

30:00.675 --> 30:02.566
That's more than we had
this morning.

30:02.568 --> 30:06.237
Nah, this place he's hiding --
it's stocked with supplies.

30:06.239 --> 30:08.330
He's got water,
he's got power.

30:08.332 --> 30:09.740
We'll be safe there.

30:09.742 --> 30:12.092
We could live there.

30:12.094 --> 30:13.469
Where is it?
Go on.

30:13.471 --> 30:15.929
Kill me.
Return me to the earth.

30:15.931 --> 30:17.356
I will live on,

30:17.358 --> 30:20.484
and, uh, someone else
will finish what I started.

30:26.108 --> 30:29.777
I know how to get you
to talk.

30:29.779 --> 30:31.328
Move.

30:33.524 --> 30:35.332
Move!

30:48.372 --> 30:51.448
I saw how upset you were
when her body went flying.

30:51.450 --> 30:53.184
Teddy.

30:56.055 --> 30:57.788
[Gunshot]

30:57.790 --> 30:59.440
What the hell?!
I'll blow
her damn head off!

30:59.442 --> 31:02.309
Go on.
What kind of a psycho
are you?

31:02.311 --> 31:04.403
Eh, you're the one who's
shooting shotgun shells

31:04.405 --> 31:06.030
into a corpse.

31:08.576 --> 31:10.076
[Gunshot]

31:10.078 --> 31:11.577
[Gun cocks]

31:11.579 --> 31:13.788
[Shell clatters]

31:13.790 --> 31:16.056
I'm sorry.
Oh, don't be.

31:16.058 --> 31:19.535
That's not my mother.

31:19.537 --> 31:21.787
Wait.
What did you say?

31:21.789 --> 31:25.165
My mother's buried on the
family farm outside Grapevine.

31:25.167 --> 31:27.651
♪♪

31:27.653 --> 31:29.503
So, you lied to us?
No.

31:29.505 --> 31:31.079
I showed you
the truth.

31:31.081 --> 31:33.507
But you were right,
Alicia.

31:33.509 --> 31:34.767
I confess.

31:34.769 --> 31:37.252
Our journey here
was not a coincidence.

31:37.254 --> 31:40.940
I was, uh, hoping
to find, um, proof

31:40.942 --> 31:43.609
that all the people that
your mother saved were dead,

31:43.611 --> 31:47.596
but I didn't suspect that
I was gonna find a living one,

31:47.598 --> 31:51.099
which, uh, proves my point
even more.

31:51.101 --> 31:55.346
♪♪

31:55.348 --> 31:57.623
Cole:
Fix the tires.

31:57.625 --> 31:59.441
We'll take the truck.

31:59.443 --> 32:03.036
♪♪

32:03.038 --> 32:06.448
Hey.

32:06.450 --> 32:08.041
I'm sorry, Alicia.

32:08.043 --> 32:10.043
I really am.

32:10.045 --> 32:12.880
I know
what your mother did for us.

32:12.882 --> 32:16.049
So, I'm gonna do something
I normally wouldn't.

32:16.051 --> 32:18.084
Come with us.

32:18.086 --> 32:19.812
I can't.

32:19.814 --> 32:23.415
I have -- I have to find out
what they're doing.

32:23.417 --> 32:24.792
Why?

32:24.794 --> 32:26.819
Because people will die
if I don't.

32:26.821 --> 32:28.712
Who? Victor?

32:28.714 --> 32:33.066
Then why isn't he out here
looking for you?

32:33.068 --> 32:34.551
That truck, that gas,

32:34.553 --> 32:36.236
we can
get the hell out of here.

32:36.238 --> 32:37.905
[Truck door opens]

32:37.907 --> 32:40.073
We drive smart, we can get
halfway across the county,

32:40.075 --> 32:43.452
far away
from whatever he's doing.

32:43.454 --> 32:46.005
And you know Victor
would be doing the same thing.

32:46.007 --> 32:50.901
♪♪

32:50.903 --> 32:54.922
I gotta warn you, Alicia,
you don't take me up on this,

32:54.924 --> 32:57.758
we got no choice
but to kill you, too.

32:57.760 --> 33:01.745
[Chuckles]

33:01.747 --> 33:04.339
Well, I guess that makes
my decision a little easier.

33:04.341 --> 33:06.934
♪♪

33:06.936 --> 33:08.560
You can go to hell.

33:08.562 --> 33:09.803
[Gun cocks]

33:09.805 --> 33:12.347
On your knees.
Now.

33:12.349 --> 33:14.925
♪♪

33:14.927 --> 33:16.777
I'll make it fast.

33:16.779 --> 33:18.829
♪♪

33:23.768 --> 33:28.605
[Birds chirping]

33:28.607 --> 33:31.275
One more chance,
old man --

33:31.277 --> 33:33.185
where are you going?

33:33.187 --> 33:36.630
♪♪

33:36.632 --> 33:39.283
Alright. Doug? Viv?

33:39.285 --> 33:40.726
It's okay.

33:40.728 --> 33:42.786
Everything I planned
will proceed

33:42.788 --> 33:45.731
even without us
being present.

33:45.733 --> 33:47.291
Are you really
going to do this?

33:47.293 --> 33:49.384
I gave you your out,
Alicia.

33:49.386 --> 33:51.628
We'll put you down.
Bury you.

33:51.630 --> 33:53.972
Oh, thank you.

33:53.974 --> 33:57.309
You two -- Well, you two
can be a warning to others.

33:57.311 --> 33:59.987
♪♪

33:59.989 --> 34:04.141
[Walkers growling]

34:04.143 --> 34:06.626
♪♪

34:06.628 --> 34:08.570
Get it over with.
We're about to have visitors.

34:08.572 --> 34:09.755
Viv? Doug?

34:09.757 --> 34:11.164
Look at me.
We can work this out.

34:11.166 --> 34:12.758
It doesn't
have to be like this.

34:12.760 --> 34:14.826
Nah, we've heard that
too many times.

34:14.828 --> 34:17.004
I'm sorry, Alicia.
I really am.

34:17.006 --> 34:19.080
Oh, they don't know
what we know.

34:19.082 --> 34:20.849
Hey, Cole.

34:20.851 --> 34:24.603
Killing people you know can be
very difficult if you're weak.

34:24.605 --> 34:26.346
Good thing
we don't know you.

34:26.348 --> 34:27.606
[Gun cocks]

34:27.608 --> 34:28.857
[Gunshot]

34:28.859 --> 34:30.667
[Growling continues]
Move.

34:30.669 --> 34:39.410
♪♪

34:39.412 --> 34:42.771
[Groaning]

34:42.773 --> 34:45.032
[Screaming]

34:45.034 --> 34:47.684
Viv. Viv.

34:47.686 --> 34:49.569
♪♪

34:49.571 --> 34:50.796
Teddy: You okay?
Yeah, you?

34:50.798 --> 34:52.815
[Chuckles]
I'm gonna miss this.

34:52.817 --> 34:55.192
[Growling continues]

34:55.194 --> 34:58.012
♪♪

34:58.014 --> 35:01.698
Don't.
I'll shoot you,
Alicia.

35:01.700 --> 35:03.717
Kill him!
Wait.

35:03.719 --> 35:04.977
Wait.

35:04.979 --> 35:06.203
Shoot him.

35:06.205 --> 35:07.596
Do it!

35:07.598 --> 35:09.056
[Walker growling]

35:09.058 --> 35:19.066
♪♪

35:19.068 --> 35:20.717
♪♪

35:20.719 --> 35:23.612
She died
so you could have a chance.

35:23.614 --> 35:26.723
Alicia, I know you don't want to
get rid of your mother, but --

35:26.725 --> 35:29.484
Shut up!
I'm not talking to you!

35:29.486 --> 35:35.082
♪♪

35:35.084 --> 35:38.326
You were supposed to
make it mean something.

35:38.328 --> 35:40.346
And you
threw it all away.

35:40.348 --> 35:46.501
♪♪

35:46.503 --> 35:49.003
Maybe it's time you listened
to your friend.

35:49.005 --> 35:51.273
♪♪

35:51.275 --> 35:53.233
Maybe it's time
you just let go --

35:53.235 --> 35:54.818
[Gunshot]

35:57.848 --> 36:07.790
♪♪

36:07.792 --> 36:17.198
♪♪

36:17.200 --> 36:20.777
You know,
you're wrong.

36:20.779 --> 36:24.539
You don't have to destroy
everything to make it better.

36:24.541 --> 36:27.208
♪♪

36:27.210 --> 36:28.894
Just people like him.

36:28.896 --> 36:38.112
♪♪

36:38.114 --> 36:41.573
[Growling]

36:42.651 --> 36:45.703
[Walker growling]

36:55.572 --> 36:58.006
Dakota: See?
It's not as hard as you think.

37:00.519 --> 37:03.170
For you.

37:03.172 --> 37:05.656
No,
not just for me.

37:05.658 --> 37:07.415
It's just how
the world is working now.

37:07.417 --> 37:09.417
That-- That's what I tried
to explain to John.

37:09.419 --> 37:11.995
I just -- I wish he'd seen it
the same way we do.

37:11.997 --> 37:13.939
I told you
there is no "we".

37:13.941 --> 37:15.924
I didn't want
to kill him.

37:15.926 --> 37:17.184
I had to do it.

37:17.186 --> 37:20.504
I want to believe
in something better.

37:20.506 --> 37:21.838
Like your mom did?

37:21.840 --> 37:23.190
[Sighs]

37:23.192 --> 37:25.767
I never had that.

37:25.769 --> 37:27.995
No one ever gave me anything
to believe in.

37:29.439 --> 37:31.014
That's not true.

37:31.016 --> 37:33.200
I tried.

37:33.202 --> 37:35.568
And you threw it away,
just like they did.

37:35.570 --> 37:36.870
[Footsteps approach]

37:36.872 --> 37:38.672
Teddy: I'm so proud of you,
Alicia.

37:38.674 --> 37:42.209
You let go of your past.
[Laughs]

37:42.211 --> 37:45.362
You -- You --
You aren't afraid to change.

37:46.623 --> 37:49.441
That doesn't mean I'm about
to fall in line behind you.

37:49.443 --> 37:52.460
You're not afraid
to question me.

37:52.462 --> 37:55.497
You really do
remind me of Mother.

37:55.499 --> 37:57.274
Did she think
you were a nutjob, too?

38:01.989 --> 38:03.730
When I was
at mortuary school,

38:03.732 --> 38:05.549
when I was trying
to figure out

38:05.551 --> 38:08.643
how I could
change things,

38:08.645 --> 38:10.570
mother found my journals
and read them.

38:10.572 --> 38:13.390
She saw the part where
I wrote about

38:13.392 --> 38:15.892
why we needed
to end everything.

38:15.894 --> 38:17.244
She thought
I was sick.

38:17.246 --> 38:18.562
No, no.

38:18.564 --> 38:21.714
"Disturbed" was the word
she used.

38:21.716 --> 38:25.010
She threatened to call
the county social services

38:25.012 --> 38:26.903
and have me committed.

38:26.905 --> 38:30.090
"That'll put an end to
your sick thoughts," she said.

38:30.092 --> 38:32.667
Yeah. [Chuckles]
"Give you a new beginning."

38:32.669 --> 38:36.096
Oh, she never knew
how right she was.

38:36.098 --> 38:38.023
I take it
you didn't listen to her.

38:38.025 --> 38:39.358
I killed her.

38:39.360 --> 38:41.268
Buried her
in the backyard.

38:41.270 --> 38:43.420
I waited
all fall and winter,

38:43.422 --> 38:47.274
worried that s-somebody
was gonna find her body.

38:47.276 --> 38:49.092
And then,
when spring rolled around,

38:49.094 --> 38:52.112
oh, the strangest
thing happened.

38:52.114 --> 38:55.282
The most beautiful
morning glories

38:55.284 --> 38:58.593
sprouted and bloomed
right over her body.

38:58.595 --> 39:01.880
That's when I realized it wasn't
enough just to change things.

39:01.882 --> 39:03.698
That was the first part.

39:03.700 --> 39:07.219
What we needed
was a new beginning.

39:07.221 --> 39:10.947
A world where people like Mother
could thrive,

39:10.949 --> 39:14.709
free from the patterns
of our broken world.

39:14.711 --> 39:18.338
♪♪

39:18.340 --> 39:20.566
How do you plan
to destroy it all?

39:20.568 --> 39:23.068
[Chuckles] Well...

39:23.070 --> 39:27.555
you certainly have earned
the truth today.

39:27.557 --> 39:30.558
That key
will launch a missile

39:30.560 --> 39:32.377
from a beached submarine

39:32.379 --> 39:35.806
washed ashore
in Galveston.

39:35.808 --> 39:38.642
That should do the job,
don't you think?

39:38.644 --> 39:46.908
♪♪

39:46.910 --> 39:48.576
I think...

39:48.578 --> 39:53.748
♪♪

39:53.750 --> 39:57.677
...that Cole isn't the only
person we need to get rid of

39:57.679 --> 39:59.271
to make things better.

39:59.273 --> 40:00.588
♪♪

40:00.590 --> 40:02.423
[Gun cocks, shell clatters]

40:02.425 --> 40:04.626
You're gonna have to
get rid of me, too.

40:04.628 --> 40:07.279
♪♪

40:12.276 --> 40:15.436
♪♪

40:15.438 --> 40:17.456
What happened
to making things right?

40:17.458 --> 40:20.274
I've been waiting a long time
to get a fresh start.

40:20.276 --> 40:21.793
Thought it was gonna be
with you and Morgan,

40:21.795 --> 40:24.037
but looks like it's gonna
have to be with him.

40:24.039 --> 40:26.039
What a surprise.
I<i> will</i> shoot you!

40:26.041 --> 40:28.525
No, no, it's okay,
Sioux.

40:28.527 --> 40:30.284
I mean, she's not gonna stop
what we're doing,

40:30.286 --> 40:31.962
and I want her alive.

40:31.964 --> 40:39.035
♪♪

40:39.037 --> 40:41.872
Morgan,
do you copy?

40:41.874 --> 40:43.874
Is anyone there?

40:43.876 --> 40:45.466
Does anyone hear me?

40:45.468 --> 40:47.653
Hello?

40:47.655 --> 40:49.303
Strand:<i> Alicia?</i>

40:49.305 --> 40:51.548
Victor?

40:51.550 --> 40:53.858
<i> Yes, it's Victor.</i>
<i> Are you okay?</i>

40:53.860 --> 40:55.786
[Vehicle approaches]
Can I trust you?

40:55.788 --> 40:57.746
<i> Of course.</i>
<i> What's wrong?</i>

40:57.748 --> 40:59.498
♪♪

40:59.500 --> 41:01.224
You need
to get to Morgan.

41:01.226 --> 41:03.526
Tell him I know what
the keys are, what they're for.

41:03.528 --> 41:05.537
He needs to find a beached
submarine near Galveston.

41:05.539 --> 41:07.580
Dakota: Don't worry.
It's just Victor.

41:07.582 --> 41:09.249
He'll be getting himself as far
away from here as possible.

41:09.251 --> 41:10.533
[Gun cocks]

41:10.535 --> 41:11.902
No!
She would've killed you.

41:11.904 --> 41:13.086
I know.

41:13.088 --> 41:14.754
That's what I was hoping
she would do

41:14.756 --> 41:17.498
because it means you are the
right person for what's to come.

41:17.500 --> 41:27.175
♪♪

41:27.177 --> 41:28.776
♪♪

41:28.778 --> 41:30.921
[Chuckles softly]

41:30.923 --> 41:40.931
♪♪

41:40.933 --> 41:42.799
♪♪

41:42.801 --> 41:46.694
[Brakes squeal]

41:46.696 --> 41:56.446
♪♪

41:56.448 --> 42:04.212
♪♪

42:04.214 --> 42:05.713
[Engine starts]

42:05.715 --> 42:10.143
Back in the 1950s,
Uncle Sam built a bunker

42:10.145 --> 42:13.630
beneath this resort
for, uh, government officials

42:13.632 --> 42:15.389
to wait out the, uh,

42:15.391 --> 42:19.560
inevitable destruction
that was coming.

42:19.562 --> 42:21.395
It was long forgotten,

42:21.397 --> 42:24.148
'til Riley
found mention of it

42:24.150 --> 42:28.611
in a newspaper article
about the hotel's bankruptcy.

42:28.613 --> 42:30.163
I...

42:30.165 --> 42:32.573
Uncle Sam was smart
about<i> what</i> was coming,

42:32.575 --> 42:35.502
just not about<i> when.</i>
[Chuckles]

42:35.504 --> 42:37.411
What's it like,
Riley, hmm?

42:37.413 --> 42:39.247
It's better than
The Holding ever was.

42:39.249 --> 42:41.582
Oh, God. Well, I suppose
I should thank you

42:41.584 --> 42:43.560
for burning
our other place down.

42:45.773 --> 42:47.164
Do they know?

42:47.166 --> 42:48.774
Your followers?

42:48.776 --> 42:50.350
Oh, they just think
they're going to live

42:50.352 --> 42:54.045
in a very well-stocked
new home.

42:54.047 --> 42:55.596
[Chuckles]
Everybody inside?

42:55.598 --> 42:56.840
We're ready.

42:56.842 --> 42:58.358
You --
You wait here, Sioux.

42:58.360 --> 43:01.252
I want -- I want to show this
to Alicia myself, okay?

43:01.254 --> 43:03.622
It's alright.
There's nothing to worry about.

43:14.960 --> 43:17.377
Oh, I wanted
to get to know you today,

43:17.379 --> 43:19.379
and I'm glad I did
because now I know

43:19.381 --> 43:22.382
you're the one
to finish what I started.

43:22.384 --> 43:24.384
I'm not
finishing anything.

43:24.386 --> 43:28.063
[Door opens]

43:28.065 --> 43:30.040
The beginning
is the end.

43:30.042 --> 43:32.392
I'm the ending,
so I can't be the beginning,

43:32.394 --> 43:33.710
but you can.

43:33.712 --> 43:35.061
What the hell
makes you think that?

43:35.063 --> 43:37.047
Because you can do
what needs to be done

43:37.049 --> 43:38.806
without losing sight
of the one thing

43:38.808 --> 43:41.475
that's gonna be in short supply
once this is all over.

43:41.477 --> 43:43.477
What's that?

43:43.479 --> 43:45.479
♪♪

43:45.481 --> 43:47.657
Hope.

43:47.659 --> 43:52.136
♪♪

43:52.138 --> 43:54.673
[Door creaks]

43:54.675 --> 43:57.567
I told them what you're dong,
and they're gonna stop you!

43:57.569 --> 44:03.815
♪♪

44:03.817 --> 44:06.667
I know this is hard to accept,
Alicia,

44:06.669 --> 44:08.502
but this
is what's happening.

44:08.504 --> 44:12.482
You are going to rebuild
the world from in there.

44:12.484 --> 44:15.085
You and I
are very much alike.

44:15.087 --> 44:16.753
I was
way ahead of my time

44:16.755 --> 44:20.164
living in a world
I was ill-suited for.

44:20.166 --> 44:22.516
But while I was inside,
the world changed

44:22.518 --> 44:25.595
into a world that was
perfectly suited for me.

44:25.597 --> 44:29.357
That's exactly
what's gonna happen...

44:29.359 --> 44:31.101
with you inside.

44:31.103 --> 44:33.670
♪♪

44:33.672 --> 44:36.106
Good luck,
Alicia.

44:36.108 --> 44:40.110
♪♪

44:40.112 --> 44:42.536
You lock me in here,

44:42.538 --> 44:45.615
I'm not gonna make the world
the way you want it to be!

44:45.617 --> 44:47.784
♪♪

44:47.786 --> 44:49.060
I know.

44:49.062 --> 44:51.304
That's what
I'm counting on.

44:51.306 --> 44:54.307
♪♪

44:54.309 --> 44:56.309
[Panting]

44:56.311 --> 45:01.031
♪♪

45:04.726 --> 45:14.402
♪♪

45:14.404 --> 45:24.379
♪♪

45:24.381 --> 45:33.396
♪♪
